{
  "doc_id": "1363",
  "text": "The present analytical approach can be easily extended to more complex phase transition regimes in the presence of moving phase transition regions (e.g. ternary and multicomponent systems [CITATION_1] ). For instance, it can be applied to ternary melts with allowance for the fact that the temperature relaxation time is much smaller than the corresponding relaxation times of solute impurities. The theory under consideration can also be used to describe the non-equilibrium solidification processes with a mushy layer [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] taking into consideration the transient behaviour of the 'solid phase-mushy layer' and 'mushy layer-liquid phase' interfaces.",
